Asperdaphne ula is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Raphitomidae.Robert Boog Watson wrote the species description in 1881. The specific name ula name comes from the Greek word οὖλος 'crisp'. Its type locality is north east of New Zealand at 37°34′S 179°22′E at a depth of 700 fathoms (4,200 ft; 1,300 m).